Slide 5 — Market insight + opportunity
The market optimized for novelty, but users actually want communication outcomes

Successful players implicitly understand that users want:

quick emotional expression without words

personalization to stand out in chats

multilingual support

fast, accurate daily texting
These needs appear repeatedly across keyboard positioning and adjacent market behavior.

But the category is still built on three fragile assumptions:

Customization drives retention
In reality, users switch back to native keyboards when performance drops or the experience becomes intrusive.

Ads can sustain the free model
In reality, excessive ad load creates direct friction in a high-frequency product.

Emoji novelty drives long-term growth
In reality, users increasingly care less about “more emoji” and more about faster communication decisions.

Opportunity:
Build AI that helps users:

react instantly

respond quickly

express tone naturally

communicate across languages

take the next action inside the conversation

Without interrupting typing.

