Slide 8 — High-level technical thinking and implementation
Facemoji AI can be implemented as a lightweight multi-agent system
1. Context layer

Inputs:

current typed text

recent conversation snippets

language detection

user preferences / style signals

2. Understanding layer

Use an LLM-based classifier to detect:

reaction intent

reply intent

translation need

creation request

action / planning intent

3. Agent layer

Route to specialized agents:

Reaction Agent
emoji, GIF, sticker, meme-style outputs

Conversation Agent
smart replies, summaries, rewrite, translation

Creation Agent
captions, meme text, emoji combos, AI expression tools

Action Agent
search, planning, recommendation cards, lightweight task help

Future: Social Twin
personalized reply style based on user tone and expression patterns

4. Model stack

LLM for generation, summarization, translation

ranking model for fast suggestion ordering

multimodal / AIGC model for image, sticker, emoji, and avatar generation

voice stack for speech-to-text input and voice-triggered assistance

5. Delivery layer

Surface outputs as:

suggestion chips

emoji strip

quick reply buttons

action cards

optional bottom sheet

6. Implementation principle

Use a hybrid approach:

On-device

ranking

autocomplete

lightweight personalization

fast latency-sensitive suggestions

Cloud

heavier generation

translation

multimodal creation

richer reasoning

Critical design rule:
AI must remain fast, optional, and non-intrusive to preserve the core keyboard experience.